  "_caveats": [
    "Share values are best-effort approximations of the EIA RECS 2020 published microdata. Use the canonical RECS 2020 microdata file (https://www.eia.gov/consumption/residential/data/2020/csv/recs2020_public_v7.csv) for exact replication.",
    "Division-level data extracted from RECS 2020 microdata (v7) using NWEIGHT-weighted tabulations by DIVISION x YEARMADERANGE. RECS 2020 splits the traditional Mountain division into Mountain North (CO, ID, MT, UT, WY) and Mountain South (AZ, NM, NV).",
    "The resolver uses share-weighted (probabilistic) fuel assignment instead of winner-take-all MODE. Each building gets a fuel type proportional to the division-level share distribution, determined by a deterministic hash of the building ID."
  ]
